      <p class="mb-6 text-slate-300">Stop gambling with manual spreadsheets. Audit your current workflow with our construction technology experts.</p>
      <%= link_to "Audit My Workflow", "#contact", class: "btn btn-primary bg-[#489DF9] hover:bg-[#3b7dc2] border-none text-white font-bold px-8" %>
    </div>

    <section id="evolution">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Evolution from Manual to Digital Precision</h2>
      <p>
        Historical estimating followed a predictable path: scale rulers and legal pads gave way to digitized takeoff software that essentially mimicked the paper process. But the industry shifted in 2025. Precision is no longer just about measuring lines on a screen; it's about <strong>Assembly-Based Estimating</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Modern custom home construction requires dynamic data. A "Wall Assembly" isn't just a square footage measurement. It's a complex recipe involving framing factors, insulation R-values, drywall waste percentages, and fastener counts. Spreadsheets struggle to maintain these relationships, while integrated systems treat them as atomic units of data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg my-12 relative">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512917774080-9991f1c4c750?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="New home construction site" class="w-full h-80 object-cover">
      <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-md px-3 py-1 rounded-lg text-[10px] text-white">
        Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@troyscanon?utm_source=llamapress&utm_medium=referral" class="underline hover:text-blue-300">Troy Mortier</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=llamapress&utm_medium=referral" class="underline hover:text-blue-300">Unsplash</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section id="accuracy-gap">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">The Accuracy Gap: Why Spreadsheets Cost 3% Margin</h2>
      <p>
        The "Accuracy Gap" is the difference between your estimated cost and the final <strong>Job Costing</strong> report. In a spreadsheet environment, this gap is usually 3-5%, often hidden within "contingency" buffers that shouldn't exist.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4 my-8">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="bg-purple-100 text-[#4C3F6D] p-1 rounded-md mr-4 mt-1"><i class="fas fa-check text-xs"></i></span>
          <div>
            <strong>Formula Atrophy:</strong> Hidden errors in complex Excel formulas are rarely caught until the accounting audit. A single broken cell in a <strong>Bill of Materials (BOM)</strong> calculation can miss thousands of board feet of lumber.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="bg-purple-100 text-[#4C3F6D] p-1 rounded-md mr-4 mt-1"><i class="fas fa-check text-xs"></i></span>
          <div>
            <strong>Bid Leveling Failures:</strong> Spreadsheets make it difficult to compare subcontractor bids side-by-side (apples-to-apples). Without a structured system, estimators miss "scope gaps"—those items neither the framer nor the roofer included in their bid.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="bg-purple-100 text-[#4C3F6D] p-1 rounded-md mr-4 mt-1"><i class="fas fa-check text-xs"></i></span>
          <div>
            <strong>Static Data:</strong> Prices for OSB and copper don't wait for your monthly spreadsheet update. Integrated systems pull live feeds from <strong>RSMeans</strong> or vendor APIs, ensuring your <strong>Preconstruction Management</strong> is based on real-world numbers.
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA 2 -->
    <div class="my-16 p-8 rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-[#4C3F6D] to-[#6d5da1] text-white shadow-xl flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-8">
