    <section id="integrated-workflows">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Takeoff to Accounting: The Integrated Workflow</h2>
      <p>
        Scaling requires a single source of truth. When your <strong>Quantity Takeoff</strong> feeds directly into your <strong>Bid Management</strong>, which then automatically generates <strong>Purchase Orders</strong> and <strong>Change Orders</strong>, you eliminate the data re-entry that plagues manual offices.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2025, the competitive advantage lies in <strong>Real-time Feedback Loops</strong>. When a field Superintendent reports a material variance, that data should automatically flag the estimating team. This allows for immediate adjustment of assembly waste factors, tightening the margin on the next 10 starts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="roi-custom-software">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">ROI of Custom Software vs. Off-the-Shelf SaaS</h2>
      <p>
        Many builders find themselves trapped in generic SaaS "Estimating Platforms." These tools often force you into rigid workflows that don't match how you actually build. You pay for 100 features and use five, while still exporting to Excel to handle your unique assemblies.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Custom software development</strong> for estimators offers a different ROI profile:
      </p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-[#4C3F6D] dark:text-[#8b5cf6] mb-2">Tailored Logic</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">Build your exact assembly recipes and waste factors into the core engine. No more workarounds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
